ign:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0p=
x;">A major theme coursing through all the conversations was the idea of Tr=
ump=E2=80=99s strength,
or at least <em>projection</em> of strength. Trump=E2=80=99s flood-the-zone=
 strategy=E2=80=94executive actions by the hour, filling screens large and =
small with a constant barrage of news=E2=80=94seems to be having the desire=
d effect. =E2=80=9CYou can see a difference between how other administratio=
ns were not doing any work, and how he is every day,=E2=80=9D said Kelly. =
=E2=80=9CHe=E2=80=99s attending events, meeting dignitaries, welcoming them=
 to the country. He=E2=80=99s taking phone calls, he=E2=80=99s doing execut=
ive orders. He=E2=80=99s still got time for his
grandkids. It=E2=80=99s like the light is on in the White House at five in =
the morning.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p=
><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong>Matt</strong>, another Tr=
ump voter from Macomb, echoed the point. =E2=80=9CIt proves that they had t=
he power to do things like that and just never did.=E2=80=9D Matt, sounding=
 like every Trump voter ever, said he respected Trump=E2=80=99s willingness=
 to take a billy club to Washington, but that he didn=E2=80=99t like his pe=
rsonal style: =E2=80=9CHe could
catch more bees with honey. He could do everything he=E2=80=99s doing in th=
e exact same way he=E2=80=99s doing it, and just not say dickhead things al=
l the time.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin:0;"><br/>In every focus group, p=
articipants (even the Harris voters) said Trump=E2=80=99s always-on visibil=
ity made for a stark contrast to Biden. =E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s cruel that th=
ey made him be president and the guy was clearly mentally declining,=E2=80=
=9D said <strong>Andrew</strong>, a college professor from Columbus who vot=
ed for Harris. Asked to describe
Biden in one word, Eric, the Pittsburgh real estate appraiser who had no ki=
nd words for Musk, answered, =E2=80=9CWeak.=E2=80=9D He said Biden=E2=80=99=
s decision to run for a second term =E2=80=9Cwas such a joke, and he was cl=
early not fit to be president for the next four years.=E2=80=9D DeAndre fro=
m Milwaukee, one of the fence-sitting voters of color, was blunt in his des=
cription of Biden: =E2=80=9CBad. Old. Terrible.=E2=80=9D Rob, the Latino en=
trepreneur from Tampa, said it was silly that Democrats pretended Biden was=
 up for the job of a second
term, when it was plain to see that he was not. =E2=80=9CHe was doing old t=
hings like falling and appearing confused. I don=E2=80=99t agree with Trump=
, but he has the perception of strength.=E2=80=9D</p></div>
