x;">If Unite the Country were looking for proof that Democrats are in despe=
rate need of a
cause, leader, brand, issue set, anything=E2=80=A6 well, they found it. The=
 Trump voters, Harris voters, and nonvoters all failed to come up with some=
thing positive to say about the party. In the Michigan groups, the moderato=
r asked voters to succinctly describe the Republican Party. Words and phras=
es that came up: =E2=80=9Cpatriotic,=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9Cstrong,=E2=80=9D =E2=
=80=9Cbuilding,=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9Cunited.=E2=80=9D Asked to play word assoc=
iation about the Democrats, the voters offered =E2=80=9Cweak,=E2=80=9D =E2=
=80=9Cout of touch,=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Cwoke.=E2=80=9D<br/><br/>Yes, most=
 of the Michigan
participants voted for Trump, but those same voters said they=E2=80=99d vot=
ed for Democratic candidates in the past, and almost all said they fondly r=
emembered when Democrats put the focus squarely on working people rather th=
an the urbane preoccupations of college-educated voters. =E2=80=9CThe Democ=
rats aren=E2=80=99t the Democrats they used to be,=E2=80=9D said Chris from=
 Bloomfield Hills. <strong>David</strong>, a father from Southfield, said h=
e liked Democrats better when Barack Obama was running. =E2=80=9CThe Democr=
ats used to be
about helping the middle class, healthcare, trying to get an affordable wag=
e. They shifted far left. They kind of forgot about their base to get these=
 extreme groups, like all these D.E.I. people. The middle class, helping th=
e unions, that used to be their bread and butter. They moved away from that=
 and that=E2=80=99s why they lost elections.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin=
:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">E=
very group was shown a handful of Kamala Harris advertisements from
the campaign=E2=80=94each focused on pocketbook issues=E2=80=94but almost n=
o one remembered seeing them. One nonvoter, <strong>Victor</strong>, who wo=
rks at a sushi restaurant in Pittsburgh, recalled seeing the Trump ad showi=
ng Harris on <em>The View</em>, unable to articulate whether she would do a=
nything differently than Biden: =E2=80=9CThe funniest one was when somebody=
 asked her what she would fix from Joe Biden, and she didn=E2=80=99t even k=
now the answer!=E2=80=9D Many <em>did</em> recall seeing the infamous=E2=80=
=94and effective=E2=80=94Trump
ads that showed Harris supporting taxpayer-funded transgender surgeries for=
 prison inmates. Eric from Pittsburgh ultimately voted for Harris, but he n=
ever forgot the ad. =E2=80=9CI know that she came from San Francisco or wha=
tever, but that was just too woke for me.=E2=80=9D DeAndre, from Milwaukee,=
 said he wished the Democrats could turn back the clock. =E2=80=9CLow price=
s, low crime, no sex changes,=E2=80=9D he said.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin=
:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">H=
arris was
talked about fondly by some voters, but even among the group of people who =
voted for her, several said they wished there had been a primary. Most said=
 they voted for her only because they didn=E2=80=99t want Trump back in off=
ice. =E2=80=9CIn my mind, Kamala didn=E2=80=99t have any policies, any plan=
s,=E2=80=9D said <strong>Matthew</strong> from Moon Township, Pennsylvania.=
 =E2=80=9CIt was just all about, =E2=80=98Stay tuned, we=E2=80=99re going t=
o fix this.=E2=80=99 But she never really said what she was going to do.=E2=
=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin:0;"><br/>A handful of
Harris voters and nonvoters said the country just isn=E2=80=99t ready to el=
ect a woman as president. <strong>Alyssa</strong>, a full-time student in M=
illersville, Pennsylvania, said that her Democratic friends wished they had=
 another choice on the ballot. =E2=80=9CDemocrats were upset that Joe Biden=
 just picked Kamala. And I think a lot of people were upset about that. The=
y were like, <em>We don=E2=80=99t have a voice</em>. And also, just to put =
it bluntly, I think a lot of people didn=E2=80=99t want to vote for a woman=
=2E
They=E2=80=99d rather not vote at all than vote for a woman who=E2=80=99s a=
 person of color.=E2=80=9D</p></div>
